{"title":"社交蒸发冷却效应","date":"2020-02-14T12:58:43.000Z","date_formatted":{"ll":"2020年2月14日","L":"2020/02/14","MM-DD":"02-14"},"thumbnail":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/idkzr/static@master/imgs/sjzflq/cover.jpg","color":"#111","link":"posts/sjzflq","comments":true,"tags":["社交"],"categories":["碎碎念"],"updated":"2020-02-14T12:58:43.000Z","content":"<p>假设有一个高级社交圈，且开放的门槛极低。那么必定会不断的吸引新成员进入，逐渐，圈内成员<strong>平均水平</strong>会不断降低。</p>\n<a id=\"more\"></a>\n<p>这时，社交圈内价值最高的成员便会<strong>离开</strong>，随后，价值第二高的人也会离开。</p>\n<p>由此，便构成了一个<strong>恶性循环</strong>，每一层的消失都将降低整个圈子的质量。</p>\n<p>最终，归于平淡。</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>该理论由硅谷的一名社交网络设计师提出。<br>\n文章内容如有侵权，请联系本人删除。</p>\n</blockquote>\n","prev":{"title":"基于Coding CI实现Hexo的持续集成与Github和Coding的同步部署","link":"posts/codingci"},"plink":"https://blog.zr.ci/posts/sjzflq/","copyright":{"author":"箴扰","link":"<a href=\"https://blog.zr.ci/posts/sjzflq/\" title=\"社交蒸发冷却效应\">https://blog.zr.ci/posts/sjzflq/</a>","license":"本博客所有文章除特别声明外，均采用(<a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">CC BY-NC-SA 4.0</a>)许可协议，转载请注明来源<a href=\"https://blog.zr.ci\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">箴扰</a>！"}}